                            <comment id="13468883" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 3 Oct 2012 21:46:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think I&apos;d prefer just converting that code to use a CQL query or two, all it cares about is &quot;is this ks/cf pair valid,&quot; which isn&apos;t a big deal to fix.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Side note: looks like some code duplication in BulkLoader.ExternalClient and BulkRecordWriter.External client, be nice to clean that up.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13480847" author="iamaleksey" created="Sat, 20 Oct 2012 22:28:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Haven&apos;t dealt with BulkRecordWriter.External/BulkLoader.ExternalClient duplication. The attached patch fixes the BulkLoader+CQL3 issue and does nothing beyond that.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please create a new issue for removing the duplication (or tell me to create it) if you still think it&apos;s worth the effort. But that would have a different priority compared to this issue, so I&apos;ve dealt with the bug first.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
